  "text": "Although toxic anterior segment syndrome was first described by Monson et al. [CITATION_1] in 1992, its exact pathophysiology still remains unclear. It is known, however, that toxic foreign substances that intra-or postoperatively enter the anterior chamber can cause inflammation.",
